<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-14T06:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-14T06:29:00-05:00" n="867" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d867">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/821</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-14T15:00:00+03:31"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            14, 1917, 3 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 16, 2.20
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2102. Answering your 1890, December 8,<note n="2" xml:id="d867fn1">See footnote 1, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_733">p. 733</ref>.</note> received to-day. Do
                                not see how can recognize Finland independence before Constituent
                                Assembly acts. Similar recognition would be demanded by Ukraine,
                                Siberia, and other provinces. Would not definitely refuse, however,
                                    <pb facs="0826" n="736" xml:id="pg_736"/> and see no objection
                                to permitting Finnish delegation to visit America.</p>
                            <p>Prompt shipment of flour, sugar, and pork recommended in my 2097<note n="1" xml:id="d867fn2">Not printed.</note> and 2098<note n="1" xml:id="d867fn3">Not printed.</note> would have a beneficial
                                effect.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_FDR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>